<emphasis box="[273,322,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">et al</emphasis>
. (2013).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1267,1582]" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,518,1339,1365]" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">Records from other places.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[524,617,1339,1365]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">CHINA</collectingCountry>
: Hong Kong, southern China, among algal turfs on salt marshes and mangrove flats— 
<bibRefCitation author="Bartsch, I." box="[309,481,1375,1401]" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" pagination="204 - 210" refId="ref8557" refString="Bartsch, I. (1990) Acarothrix palustris gen. et spec. nov. (Halacaroidea, Acari), ein Bewohner der Salzwiesen Sudchinas. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 224, 204 - 210." type="journal article" year="1990">Bartsch (1990)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[495,657,1375,1401]" name="Singapore" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">SINGAPORE</collectingCountry>
: Pandan River, southern coast of Singapore, among green algae and epibiota on 
<taxonomicName box="[283,393,1411,1437]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Avicennia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[283,393,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">Avicennia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
