<bibRefCitation author="Bartsch, I." box="[768,937,1411,1438]" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" pagination="83 - 92" refId="ref9198" refString="Bartsch, I. (2006) Copidognathines (Acari: Halacaridae) in mangroves of Singapore. I. Description of three species. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 54, 83 - 92." type="journal article" year="2006">Bartsch (2006)</bibRefCitation>
; End of Lim Chu Kang Road, northern coast of Singapore, from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kutzing" authorityYear="1843" box="[370,505,1447,1473]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Cladophora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[370,505,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">Cladophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mats on muddy and sandy sediment in mangrove areas— 
<bibRefCitation author="Bartsch, I." box="[1153,1324,1447,1474]" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" pagination="83 - 92" refId="ref9198" refString="Bartsch, I. (2006) Copidognathines (Acari: Halacaridae) in mangroves of Singapore. I. Description of three species. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 54, 83 - 92." type="journal article" year="2006">Bartsch (2006)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
